Major roads, airports, and markets were on Tuesday deserted in Abuja and Lagos following the Federal Government’s restriction order on movement. The government said the 14-day restriction was in a bid to curb the transmission of the coronavirus in the country. In its last update, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control said the country currently has 135 confirmed cases. See photos:  Photos by: Olatunji Obasa  and Olufemi Dawodu